%% State Machine: docs-workflows-refactoring-v2
%% taskId: 5127ee0c-0fad-4088-a2bc-e7c590595738
%%
%% decisions:
%%   D1: Use rmdir (not rm -rf) for empty dir deletion - prevents accidental data loss
%%   D2: Delete inner-most nested dirs before outer dirs - avoids "directory not empty" errors
%%   D3: Baseline file count captured before any mutation - enables AC-6 zero-loss verification
%%   D4: Separate empty-root-dir and empty-category-dir phases - isolates failure domains
%%   D5: CreateTargetDirs before MoveFiles - ensures destination exists, prevents move failures
%%   D6: MoveDirs uses git mv for uncategorized dirs - preserves git history
%%   D7: Verify phase compares file count against baseline - deterministic L1 gate

stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> Baseline

    Baseline: Capture file count (expect 1902)
    Baseline --> DeleteEmptyRootDirs: count == 1902

    DeleteEmptyRootDirs: rmdir 9 empty duplicate root dirs
    DeleteEmptyRootDirs --> DeleteEmptyCategoryDirs: 9 dirs removed, 0 files lost

    DeleteEmptyCategoryDirs: rmdir 13 empty category-side dirs
    DeleteEmptyCategoryDirs --> MoveDirs: 13 dirs removed, inner-first order

    MoveDirs: git mv 7 uncategorized dirs to categories
    MoveDirs --> CreateTargetDirs: 7 dirs relocated under feature/investigation/fix

    CreateTargetDirs: mkdir target dirs for loose .md files
    CreateTargetDirs --> MoveFiles: destination dirs exist

    MoveFiles: git mv 19 loose .md files into category dirs
    MoveFiles --> Verify: 19 files moved

    Verify: Recount files, validate structure
    Verify --> [*]: file count == 1902 AND no loose files remain

    Baseline --> FailBaseline: count != 1902
    DeleteEmptyRootDirs --> FailRmdir: dir not empty (unexpected files)
    DeleteEmptyCategoryDirs --> FailNested: ordering error or non-empty dir
    MoveDirs --> FailMove: target category missing
    MoveFiles --> FailMove: destination dir missing
    Verify --> FailVerify: file count mismatch or loose files remain

    FailBaseline: Abort - baseline assumption violated
    FailRmdir: Abort - investigate unexpected contents
    FailNested: Abort - re-check nesting order
    FailMove: Rollback via git checkout
    FailVerify: Rollback via git checkout

    FailBaseline --> [*]
    FailRmdir --> [*]
    FailNested --> [*]
    FailMove --> [*]
    FailVerify --> [*]
